  "text": "Invasion assay. Chemotactic cell invasion assay was performed using 24-well Transwell units with an 8-mm pore size polycarbonate filter (Millipore) according to the method described previously [CITATION_1] . Each lower compartment of the Transwell contained 600 ml 0.5 % FBS as chemoattractant or 0.5 % BSA as negative control in RPMI 1640. The upper side of a polycarbonate filter was coated with Matrigel (5 mg/ml in cold medium) to form a continuous thin layer. Prior to addition of the cell suspension, the dried layer of Matrigel matrix was rehydrated with medium without FBS for 2 h at room temperature. Cells preincubated with antibodies or inhibitors ( 110 5 ) were suspended in 0.1 ml RPMI 1640 containing 0.1 % BSA and added into the upper compartment of the Transwell unit and incubated for 36 h at 37 8C in a humidified atmosphere containing 5 % CO 2 . Cells remaining in the upper compartment were completely removed with gentle swabbing. The number of cells that had invaded through the filter into the lower compartment was determined using a colorimetric crystal violet assay.",
